03:12.684 --> 03:14.652
Do you hear that?

03:14.654 --> 03:15.886
Hear what?

03:18.289 --> 03:19.389
Listen.

03:24.996 --> 03:26.463
Come on.

03:35.706 --> 03:37.174
What?

03:37.176 --> 03:39.809
That's my father's automobile.

03:39.811 --> 03:41.511
Henry has got ours.

03:41.513 --> 03:42.753
Isn't that your family's horse?

04:19.415 --> 04:21.482
You'll find the words on page 36.

04:22.618 --> 04:23.618
This isn't right.

04:23.620 --> 04:24.953
Sit down, Esther.

04:24.955 --> 04:26.521
You shouldn't even be here.

04:26.523 --> 04:27.889
This is man's business.

04:27.891 --> 04:28.890
It's about the children.

04:28.892 --> 04:29.991
Mother.

04:29.993 --> 04:31.526
And that makes it woman's business.

04:31.528 --> 04:34.128
A mother's heart is a tender thing.

04:34.130 --> 04:36.030
These good men are trying to spare

04:36.032 --> 04:39.066
every mother in this town.

04:39.068 --> 04:41.436
War is a beast, yes.

04:41.438 --> 04:42.318
It consumes the young.

04:44.206 --> 04:46.774
I offer a shield

04:46.776 --> 04:48.408
for the children of the righteous.

04:48.410 --> 04:51.245
Trading lives? Making pacts?

04:51.247 --> 04:52.579
That's not God's way.

04:52.581 --> 04:54.749
Oh? You speak for God?

04:54.751 --> 04:56.350
I speak for the children.

04:56.352 --> 04:58.352
It's your vow but they'll
be the ones to pay.

04:58.354 --> 04:59.620
The men decide what's best

04:59.622 --> 05:01.255
for the women and the children.

05:01.257 --> 05:03.390
That's the way it's in the Bible.

05:03.392 --> 05:04.391
Right, Reverend?

05:04.393 --> 05:06.226
From Genesis to Revelation.

05:09.697 --> 05:11.931
Thomas Rivers, you know this is wrong.

05:11.933 --> 05:14.601
Esther, you know what's
happening over there.

05:14.603 --> 05:15.935
It's a slaughter.

05:15.937 --> 05:18.905
Now the boys in this town
are heading right into it.

05:18.907 --> 05:21.040
Ravenswood has suffered enough.

05:21.042 --> 05:22.776
We need to sign this pact.

05:22.778 --> 05:24.343
For the good of us all.

05:24.345 --> 05:25.979
We've all had so much war, sister.

05:25.981 --> 05:27.280
As I was saying,

05:27.282 --> 05:28.915
you'll find the words on page 36...

05:41.762 --> 05:44.196
Foolish men trying to save the children

05:44.198 --> 05:46.632
from the war that other men started.

05:46.634 --> 05:48.401
Had I know Caleb and Miranda were there,

05:48.403 --> 05:51.003
I would have gathered
them up and left town.

05:51.005 --> 05:54.239
I will set this right... somehow.

05:54.241 --> 05:56.275
Is she talking about the
night the pact was made?

05:56.277 --> 05:57.342
I think so.

05:57.344 --> 06:00.378
So you were there? The other you?

06:00.380 --> 06:03.348
That other guy is just my ancestor.

06:03.350 --> 06:05.583
And Esther was the mother
of the original Miranda,

06:05.585 --> 06:07.585
and the man we found and eloped with her

06:07.587 --> 06:09.587
was original Caleb's father,

06:09.589 --> 06:11.222
Thomas Rivers.

06:11.224 --> 06:14.326
But they were on opposite
sides of the pact.

06:14.328 --> 06:17.329
How did they end up down there together?

06:17.331 --> 06:18.452
Let me see Esther's journal.

06:21.701 --> 06:24.502
That's as far as we got
while you were in Ravenswood.

06:24.504 --> 06:25.970
This preacher must have offered

06:25.972 --> 06:27.738
the town elders some sort of deal.

06:27.740 --> 06:29.073
Maybe they knew what it
was, maybe they didn't,

06:29.075 --> 06:31.275
but it ended up protecting
the soldiers of the town.

06:31.277 --> 06:32.576
Like it did my mom.

06:32.578 --> 06:34.645
All it cost was five innocent lives.

06:34.647 --> 06:36.113
Five per war.

06:36.115 --> 06:38.115
Not quite.

06:38.117 --> 06:40.517
Four of you are still alive.

06:42.321 --> 06:43.561
We're going to keep it that way.

06:45.357 --> 06:46.757
There's something else.

06:48.059 --> 06:49.226
What?

06:49.228 --> 06:51.628
I'm back on a short leash.

06:51.630 --> 06:52.763
What do you mean?

06:52.765 --> 06:54.531
I can't leave the grounds.

06:54.533 --> 06:56.233
After you left I was back here.

06:56.235 --> 06:57.668
We think it has to do with those jars.

06:57.670 --> 07:00.136
Someone was digging around
Miranda's gravestone...

07:00.138 --> 07:01.404
maybe Collins dug her up,

07:01.406 --> 07:03.773
put another lock of her
hair in one of those jars.

07:03.775 --> 07:05.175
If you leave town for three days

07:05.177 --> 07:06.776
you're going to miss some stuff.

07:06.778 --> 07:08.311
So Collins knows what happened.

07:08.313 --> 07:10.213
That Miranda was able to leave.

07:11.949 --> 07:14.817
Guess you're stuck with me.

07:14.819 --> 07:16.919
We're going to find out
who this preacher was...

07:16.921 --> 07:18.320
what he had to gain from this curse

07:18.322 --> 07:19.756
and how he had the power to enforce it.

07:19.758 --> 07:21.391
Maybe we can reverse engineer the pact,

07:21.393 --> 07:23.760
break it, and the curse.

07:23.762 --> 07:25.862
Does she mention a name at all?

07:26.997 --> 07:28.097
It's right there.

07:30.734 --> 07:33.769
Don't know if I'm saying this right...

07:33.771 --> 07:35.437
Gabriel Abaddon.

07:49.286 --> 07:51.185
Think you said it right.

07:51.187 --> 07:55.876
Is there anything left?

